    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static RakeAPI getInstance(Context context,
                                  java.lang.String token,
                                  java.lang.Boolean isDevServer)
        Deprecated. As of 0.3.17, replaced by getInstance(Context, String, Env, Logging)}
        Create RakeAPI instance. (singleton per token)
        Parameters:
        context - Android Application Context
        token - Rake Token
        isDevServer - indicate whether RakeAPI send log to development server or live server If false used, RakeAPI will send log to development server (pg.rake.skplanet.com) If true is used, RakeAPI will send log to live server (rake.skplanet.com).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if RakeAPI called multiple times with different isDevServer value.

      • getInstance

        public static RakeAPI getInstance(Context context,
                                  java.lang.String token,
                                  RakeAPI.Env env,
                                  RakeAPI.Logging loggingMode)
        Create RakeAPI instance. (singleton per token)
        Parameters:
        context - Android Application Context
        token - Rake Token
        env - indicate whether RakeAPI send log to development server or live server If RakeAPI.Env.DEV used, RakeAPI will send log to development server (pg.rake.skplanet.com) If RakeAPI.Env.LIVE used, RakeAPI will send log to live server (rake.skplanet.com)
        loggingMode - Logging.ENABLE or Logging.DISABLE
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if RakeAPI called multiple times with different RakeAPI.Env.
